HEADWORD: Seismometry
<hw>Seis*mom"e*try</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The mensuration
of such phenomena of earthquakes as can be expressed in numbers, or by
their relation to the coordinates of space.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seismoscope</ent>⟦br⟧
